      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "All three FEA codes (FDA in-house, Ansys 2021 R2, DePuy Synthes proprietary solver) are operated under documented quality management systems with version-controlled inputs and outputs. Software qualification records are on file for each code version used in the ensemble."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems with analytical solutions (cantilever beam, Hertzian contact) were solved by each code; maximum deviation from analytical reference was 0.8%, confirming correct code implementation for the relevant physics."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence studies were performed for each geometry in the ensemble. The quantity of interest (peak von Mises stress at screw-rod interface) changed by less than 2% between the medium and fine mesh; the fine mesh was adopted for all production runs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson residual convergence tolerances were set to 1e-6 for force and displacement norms. Iterative solver residuals were logged and confirmed below tolerance for all 11 construct simulations; no load-step bisections were required."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Model setup procedures are documented in a controlled simulation protocol. An independent analyst reproduced three of the eleven construct simulations from the protocol alone; results agreed within 0.5% of the primary analyst outputs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic material models with titanium alloy properties (Ti-6Al-4V, E=114 GPa, ν=0.34) are appropriate for the sub-yield loading regime of the F1717 compression-bending test. Contact at the screw-rod interface is modelled with a Coulomb friction coefficient of 0.2, consistent with published tribological data for titanium-on-titanium."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Screw and rod geometry was derived from CMM measurements of production hardware (mean dimensional deviation <0.02 mm). Material certificates and tensile coupon data from the same material lots used for experimental constructs were used to populate model inputs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs were assembled from production-representative hardware by trained laboratory technicians following the F1717 standard. Sample traceability was maintained through lot numbers; no outliers were excluded from the comparison dataset."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single load rate (5 mm/min) and ambient temperature (23 ± 2 °C) per the F1717 protocol. No variation in test conditions (e.g., elevated temperature, varied load rate) was explored, limiting the breadth of the validation evidence. This factor falls below the required level and constitutes the sole credibility gap identified in this assessment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Measured geometry, torque-preload relationships, and friction coefficients from the experimental constructs were used directly as model inputs, ensuring high fidelity between the physical test configuration and the computational model."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Predicted construct stiffness and yield load were compared against experimental measurements using the validation metric defined in ASME V&V 10.1. The model error was within ±8% for stiffness and ±6% for yield load across all eleven constructs, satisfying the pre-specified acceptance threshold of ±15%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load under compression-bending are the primary mechanical performance indicators specified in ASTM F1717 and are directly linked to the clinical performance question of construct stability under physiological loading."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "The validation activities replicate the F1717 compression-bending test configuration in both geometry and loading, directly matching the simulation scenario. The two-laboratory design increases confidence in reproducibility of the experimental reference data."
    }
  ],
